CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 1, 1960, pg. 21, reads: "Victory Grin - Pirate pitcher Diomedes Olivo recently recalled from the minors, had a chance to enjoy the parade festivities in downtown Pittsburgh Sunday night as he took part in victory celebration. The hard-throwing relief hurler from the Dominican Republic may get a chance with the Bucs in 1961. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball player Diomedes Olivo riding in back of car in parade for celebration of 1960 National League Championship, Downtown
